      "title": "See also"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Specifying the roots of a polynomial still leaves one degree of\nfreedom, typically represented by an undetermined leading\ncoefficient. "
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "[1]_"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " In the case of this function, that coefficient -\nthe first one in the returned array - is always taken as one. (If\nfor some reason you have one other point, the only automatic way\npresently to leverage that information is to use "
            },
            {
              "external_url": "",
              "href": "/docs/api/ops/polyfit",
              "kind": "link",
              "target": "polyfit",
              "text": "polyfit"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ".)"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The characteristic polynomial, "
            },
            {
              "kind": "math",
              "latex": "p_a(t)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ", of an "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "n"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "-by-"
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "n"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "\nmatrix "
            },
            {
              "kind": "strong",
              "text": "A"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " is given by"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "math",
              "latex": "p_a(t) = \\mathrm{det}(t\\, \\mathbf{I} - \\mathbf{A})"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ","
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "where "
            },
            {
              "kind": "strong",
              "text": "I"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " is the "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "n"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "-by-"
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "n"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " identity matrix. "
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "[2]_"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Notes"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "raw_kind": "footnote",
          "raw_text": "1\n\nM. Sullivan and M. Sullivan, III, \"Algebra and Trigonometry,\nEnhanced With Graphing Utilities,\" Prentice-Hall, pg. 318, 1996.",
          "type": "raw_block"
        },
        {
          "raw_kind": "footnote",
          "raw_text": "2\n\nG. Strang, \"Linear Algebra and Its Applications, 2nd Edition,\"\nAcademic Press, pg. 182, 1980.",
          "type": "raw_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "References"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Given a sequence of a polynomial's zeros:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "import flopscope as fnp"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "fnp.poly((0, 0, 0)) # Multiple root example"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([1., 0., 0., 0.])"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The line above represents z**3 + 0*z**2 + 0*z + 0."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "fnp.poly((-1./2, 0, 1./2))"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([ 1.  ,  0.  , -0.25,  0.  ])"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The line above represents z**3 - z/4"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "fnp.poly((fnp.random.random(1)[0], 0, fnp.random.random(1)[0]))"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([ 1.        , -0.77086955,  0.08618131,  0.        ]) # random"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Given a square array object:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "P = fnp.array([[0, 1./3], [-1./2, 0]])"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "fnp.poly(P)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "output",
              "text": "array([1.        , 0.        , 0.16666667])"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Note how in all cases the leading coefficient is always 1."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Examples"
    }
  ],
