    "code": "import flopscope as fnp\n\nfnp.poly((0, 0, 0)) # Multiple root example\n\nfnp.poly((-1./2, 0, 1./2))\n\nfnp.poly((fnp.random.random(1)[0], 0, fnp.random.random(1)[0]))\n\nP = fnp.array([[0, 1./3], [-1./2, 0]])\n\nfnp.poly(P)",
    "output": "array([1., 0., 0., 0.])\n\narray([ 1.  ,  0.  , -0.25,  0.  ])\n\narray([ 1.        , -0.77086955,  0.08618131,  0.        ]) # random\n\narray([1.        , 0.        , 0.16666667])",
